annotation.TEXT: Oh, yes it is, and it revealed a star on the map!
Uh, oh. Another Big Boo. No big deal, although I'm not going to try to slide-kill this guy.
Now, I bet I know where this P-switch is to be used... (I probably didn't need to double grab, but whatever.)
Not bothering with the flower. If it was a cape, I'd probably have gone for it.
I think I should go up, but I'll want to bring the spring with me if I can...
Just making sure there aren't any other offscreen secrets before I go down the pipe.
I'll just grab me another feather here since I lost one earlier.
Ouch...
It's time for episode 21 of Super SIG World 21! I wonder if anything special will happen today? Well, let's look at the voting results first:
Now, we know a star works on them, from a bonus room earlier in the game. Hmm... You can't eat them...
Being just to the right of center should be sufficient to avoid cannonfire. There's no need to be right up against the screen edge and risk getting smacked by some other incoming hazard!
Aha! They're slide-killable! But, are there any other ways to kill them?
Uhh... Did that door send me backwards? Yeah, I think it sent me backwards, which means I missed something somewhere...
Watch out for the boo chains.
What about ice blocks?
Oh, hey there, Big Boo! How's it going?
Still have no clue what that upper room is for... Maybe it's just there to mess with my mind...
Oh, it's actually a Reznor battle, which my flower is useless against! Well, they still shouldn't be a problem.
To be continued...
Yeah, there's a secret in the ceiling there that can be revealed by tossing the key at that spot. (If you were really observant, you might've noticed this at about 7:18 in this video.)
Just barely avoided another hit there. (That one wasn't quite fully faded in when I entered the pipe.)
Just a Yoshi coin, but it was kind of obvious, so I wouldn't expect much more than that.
I'll just take another look through the room here...
Okay, so they got cannons too, but... Because of the autoscroll speed, if I stay on the right half of the screen, I shouldn't have to worry about any of them.
Looks like I'll need to find an ON/OFF block to reach that Yoshi coin, but what's with the upper room here? Darned if I know...
"After Bowser is toast, I'll do the same thing to those morons working at YouTube!"
That opens up the fortress, which I guess I'll be starting with next time! But, before I end the video, I'm going to go look for that missing Yoshi coin in the ghost house...
Oh, yeah. Make sure this is set correctly, so that I can get to where I want to be.
It's nice to know they don't hurt Yoshi.
It leads to boss time! Wow, really?
Outta the way, boney!
Nope, I can't enter that pipe, and it was probably not a good idea to try!
Aww... It's a teleport, as I suspected, so no spring for me.
Well, knowing that this game likes to hide some stuff just offscreen, I'm going to fly around and see if I can find something...
Hmm... Do I want to hit that ON/OFF block again? Maybe, but I have no idea...
Whoa! How did I not get burned there? Honestly, I thought I was gonna get barbequed!
A few more coins and another feather are in these blocks.

Now, just so you guys know, this star is an actual level. I wanted to take a peek at where it would send me, thinking it was a warp, but then I saw "MARIO START!", so I quickly rewound back to the map here.
Coins! So many coins! Just like in the ghost ship!
And there's the key I was expecting to see... along with a plethora of ghosts! Watch out!
Yep! Which means that things like shells probably work as well.
But first... Let's see what other ways I can find to assassinate those obnoxious purple buzzies! (I'm curious about this one, too.)
Yep. Now I can get this Yoshi coin, and I should also be able to go past the door further on now.
No Yoshis because they get airsick.
And that's how I discovered this really well-hidden secret. First of all, look at my reserve item. Do you notice something odd as I move around here?
Okay, it is. That's good. But where's the last Yoshi coin? Is it offscreen somewhere around here?
7-Fort
Well, I hope the goal is right through this door, because my time limit's getting low!
Yeah, that was unusually easy... I was expecting maybe a higher HP count for him or something, but no. It's just the regular run-of-the-mill boss with easy to avoid munchers below.
Looks like I reached the end. I think I'll equip my flower in case there are more Hammer Bro family members to fight.
Dive bombing didn't work, but what about cape-sliding? Can I even line that up correctly? (If I get hurt, there's a feather in one of those ? blocks that I can use.)
Okay, so I still have to pay attention for certain cannons, but my trusty cape should help keep me protected!
My fireballs just pass through them, and spin jumps don't affect them...
Hello! I heard the distinct sound of a switch there! Yeah, there's a switch just above where the Yoshi coin there was! Very sneaky, game!
Now, let's go take on the airships level, 7-5!
Piece of cake! Chocolate cake? Maybe.
...a secret door appears! (So, double grabbing was pointless, as I can't bring the key in with me. Whatever.)
Uhh, how far does this go?

Hitting that spot twice with the key will cause a P-switch to drop down. (When I initially found this, my time was almost up, so I just restarted the level and quickly made my way to this point again.)
Uh, oh. Please don't hit me. Thank you.
I guess I could fly up and get some more coins from the bottom of this chunk, but I'm not going to waste too much time with that.
So, if I stomp the P-switch in this upper room that was messing with my mind...
I still have no idea what the point of this upper room is...

Well, you won't believe what I found (or, maybe you will)... I searched practically everywhere in the level, trying everything I could think of, and even going so far as to toss the key at practically every wall and ceiling tile.
Still have no idea what I'm missing...
Vote now, and next time, we'll see where the votes take me!
Obvious secret in the upper-left.
I assume that toggled those blocks to the right, so let's see what I can reach now...
There's Yoshi coin number 4.
Just because.
I wonder if there are any levels left that I can bring Yoshi into?
7-Star
Also, due to the key being forced into slot 0 (I think) from the pipe transition, the Big Boos in this room (which can only exist in slot 0) won't spawn while the key is present.
Seems like the SMB3 airships level from world 8. The cape just makes this fairly easy... maybe.
That, of course, leads to the ghost house. No surprise here. So, now let's explore the ghost house!
A floating door above silver munchers that I obviously need to get into. Knowing this game, there's probably a key later on in the level...
I have no idea...
So, I guess next time, I won't necessarily be heading to the fortress first! You guys get to vote on whether I do the fortress next, or the star level (whatever it's called) next!
Okay, well, I think I've wasted enough time here.
Let's see where this pipe leads...
Maybe the main difficulty was in finding this boss in the first place... Now, is this indeed a secret exit?
Yeah, I think I'll take an extra feather this time. Who knows? It could come in handy in some special way later on!

1 vote for GlitchMr to find out how to get the old channel design back, 1 vote for Mario to yell out, "After Bowser is toast, I'll do the same thing to those morons working at YouTube!" near the end of this video, 1 vote for Mario to go back in time to when whoever got the ideas for the new channels was coming up with them and give them a shell to the face,
Okay, we're at the bottom, with three Yoshi coins! So that means there were seven total in this level!
Yeah, it's a Big Boo Boss battle! It looks pretty easy, but does this mean that this is a secret exit?

1 vote to eat as many poison mushrooms as possible as quickly as possible, 1 vote to find any ways I can to assassinate those obnoxious purple buzzy beetles, 2 votes for 3-1, 4 votes for the ghost house, and 10 votes for 7-5! Alright, so I guess I'm going to 7-5, the airships level!
